So according to the formula, for n = 2, the coefficient of \( \tan^1 x \) is: \( a_1 = (-1)^{(1 - 1)/2} \binom{2}{1} = (-1)^0 \times 2 = 2 \), which is correct. Similarly, for n = 4: The coefficient of \( \tan^3 x \) is: \( a_3 = (-1)^{(3 - 1)/2} \binom{4}{3} = (-1)^1 \times 4 = -4 \), which matches. Therefore, this formula holds for both odd and even n.
